{
  "stem": "20800.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But names of parents and things, I change.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So when I went to them, we have to have two witnesses.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We went to a solicitor, and Iagunova, that's another girl who helped me, and they both went at night to the solicitor and they signed the documents.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The solicitor wrote in Russia, that we Chotowa, this and that, lived in Krasnodar, and that he is from Krasnodar.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He now resides and does our two signature.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that was good enough document to survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I took this document.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course, with this document, I went back to my family, to my sisters.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But that wasn't enough.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had to go to German authorities to get the same thing in German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So I went to German authorities.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Gave them, this is my document.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I would like to have it translated in German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they did it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So that's how we, that means me and my sisters and mother, stayed alive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We lived on those documents.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "If somebody came and asked, we had something to show that we're not a Jew.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mom was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because she was a bit Semitic so.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But dad was on the front, he was in the army.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he was a Russian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father Russian, and mom, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] [NON-ENGLISH], I don't know how it's in English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As yes, as Chotowa, non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody knew that we're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe somebody suspect us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they couldn't do a thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we have a document to prove it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's how we survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that was the first.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, when we-- when I had documents, I was gutsy enough to get to the underground organization too.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By then we knew what Germans do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We knew he kills all Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
